{
  "text": "Although FSHD1 had been invariably been associated only with the 4q locus, Lemmers et al. described a pedigree in which the disease-causative allele is a short D4Z4 array on chromosome 10qter [CITATION_1] . Owing to a de novo translocation event, the diseaseassociated 10q array ends distally in 4qter sequence complete with the ATTAAA sequence. This combination of a shortened 10q D4Z4 array in combination with a functional PAS is therefore sufficient for the development of FSHD and argues strongly against a primary mechanism that acts via a cis effect of D4Z4 contraction on more proximal 4q35 genes.",
